            <span id="Chapter_Title_Mod">
            The Year Leading Up to Enlistment
            </span>
            <span id="Contributor_Name_Mod">
            bill roos
            </span>
            <span id="First_Paragraph_Mod">
            Because I had taken a heavy class schedule my junior year, I did not need a lot of credits to graduate, so my senior year was relatively light. I worked the first two periods, came to school for the 3rd period which was American History, then took lunch followed by choir at no credit (because I had band as well during the 6th period, and you could receive credit for only one music class). For 5th period I took Art. The only homework I had was for American History where we had to write a 5000 word theme on some part of American History for our final semester’s grade. I wrote my theme on Alaska, and got an A. A pretty easy final year. <br />
            </span>
            <!--div id="boxmodex3" class="clearfix">
                <div class="ChapterVideoDivMod">
                    <div class="ChapterVideoMod">
                        <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/124071486" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>
